@node 2 "FAtEStAts v1.0 - iNtR0dUCti0N"

tRiflEX, CNet's No.1 is back with FAtEStAtS, the coolest User Status
and System Status Doors on CNet! With a little bit Inspiration of some /X
Doors I thought the usual Status Command is simply BORING, we need more
Infos, more and more... well, then I got limited by the Screen Height :)
Anyway check out "FateUStat.pic" and "FateSStat.pic" which should accompany
this Archive, or better install FAtEStAtS immediately :)
@endnode
@node 3 "FAtEStAtS V1.o - iNStAllAti0N"

Copy "FateUStat" and "FateSStat" to your "PFiles:" Directory.

Start up your favourite Text Editor and load "cnet:bbsmenu".
Go to Section 2 (avaible everywhere) and alter the "STatus" line to /STatus
or \STatus or whatever. Next jump to the end of this Section and add:

     STatus    |#0PFiles:FateUStat}
     SysSTatus |#0PFiles:FateSStat}
                ^
Where these ----' Chars are CTRL-Q's.

Save the File and go to Section 30 (Computer Types).
Remove the leading TAB at the Start of each Line and copy then the whole
Section except for the "30; Computer Types..." Line into the Block Buffer.

Clear the File.

Now set up the Configfile for the FAtEStAtS. Write THE HIGHEST PORT NUMBER
into Line 1. Then write a short "Description" for each Port, e.g. "Local
Bus" for Port 0 (your own) or "Terbo Terror" if you have a v32terbo modem.
Don't forget: Line 1 is not the Number of Ports you have, but the highest
Port Number !!!

Then write the Number of Computer Types you have into the next Line.
Next paste the Block (which should still contain the computer types...).

In the next Line write a Summary of all Ports for the System Stats, e.g.
"2 Duals and 1 ZyXEL".

If your BBS belongs to a specific Organization (like tRiflEX :) place its
Name in the next Line. Otherwise write something like "Independent".

The next Line contains the Names of your CoSysops. If you have none write
"None" or something like that.

The last Line is meant to be a short Description of your Hardware.

Note that all Strings are limited to 24 Chars. Everything longer will be
cut off.
Save as "PFiles:FateStats.cfg". Here is an example Configfile:

--- cut here ---
2
Local Bus
Terbo Terror
Fast, faster, V.fast
6
Amiga
IBM PC
OS/2
Apple Macintosh
UNIX
Other Computer
1 Terbo and a V.fast
tRiflEX
None!
A4000'40, 1.3 Gig HD, 8MB
--- cut here ---

It shouldn't be that difficult, if so, don't hestitate to contact me!
@endnode
